    <h2>Yercaud</h2>
    <p>Yercaud is a hill station in Salem District, in Tamil Nadu, India. 
    It located in the Shevaroys range of hills in the Eastern Ghats; the Yercaud hill area is called the Shevaroy Hills. 
    It is situated at an altitude of 1515 metres (4970 ft) above sea level. 
    Coffee and citrus fruits, most notably oranges, are grown in abundance apart from bananas, pears and jackfruit. 
    Scenically, Yercaud is as enchanting and picturesque as the hill stations on the Western ghats and trekking here can be one of the most pleasurable ways to pass time.</p>
